CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 7, 1962, pg. A10, reads: "New Sorors Initiated - Kappa Chapter of Chi Eta Phi, professional national nursing sorority, initiated four new sorors into the chapter last Saturday evening at a dinner meeting at the Greene Hearth. Left to right, seated: Soror Mary Daily, dean of pledgees; Soror Mamie Garland, basileus, and Soror Bessie Cephas, founder of the Pittsburgh chapter. Standing: New Sorors Marian Johnson, Lillian Wilkerson, Eleanor Chilton and Elsie Carter. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of members of Kappa chapter of Chi Eta Phi nursing sorority, seated from left: Mary Daily, Mamie Garland, Bessie Cephas; standing: Marian Johnson, Lillian Wilkerson, Eleanor Chilton, and Elsie Carter, gathered behind table in Greene Hearth
